.TH NHOPKG-REPOS 8 "@RELEASEDATE@" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "Nhopkg Manual"
.SH NAME
nhopkg-repos \- create, maintain, and sign nhopkg binary package repositories
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nhopkg-repos
\fB\-g\fR, \fB\-\-create-repo\fR \fI<dir>\fR
.br
.B nhopkg-repos
\fB\-A\fR, \fB\-\-add-to-repo\fR [\fB\-\-repo\-dir\fR \fI<dir>\fR] \fI<package.nho>...\fR
.br
.B nhopkg-repos
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-sign\fR [\fB\-k\fR \fI<key>\fR] \fI<package.nho>\fR
.br
.B nhopkg-repos
\fB\-\-sign-all\fR [\fB\-k\fR \fI<key>\fR] \fB\-\-repo\-dir\fR \fI<dir>\fR
.br
.B nhopkg-repos
\fB\-\-verify\fR \fI<package.nho>\fR
.br
.B nhopkg-repos
\fB\-\-keygen\fR [\fB\-\-batch\fR] [\fB\-\-passphrase-file\fR \fI<file>\fR]
.br
.B nhopkg-repos
\fB\-\-import-key\fR \fI<file|url>\fR
.br
.B nhopkg-repos
\fB\-\-export-key\fR [\fI<id>\fR]
.br
.B nhopkg-repos
\fB\-\-list-keys\fR
.br
.B nhopkg-repos
\fB\-\-remove-key\fR \fI<id>\fR
.br
.B nhopkg-repos
\fB\-\-add-repo\fR \fI<name>\fR \fI<url>\fR
.br
.B nhopkg-repos
\fB\-\-remove-repo\fR \fI<name>\fR
.br
.B nhopkg-repos
\fB\-\-list-repos\fR
.br
.B nhopkg-repos
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
.br
.B nhopkg-repos
\fB\-\-version\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBnhopkg-repos\fR creates and maintains binary package repositories for nhopkg
and provides GPG signing and verification for packages and repository metadata.
It organizes \fI.nho\fR packages into subdirectories by repository type
(core, extra, multilib) based on the \fB# Repository:\fR field in each package's
nhoid metadata.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Repository Management
.TP
.B \-g, \-\-create-repo \fI<dir>\fR
Create a new repository structure from \fI.nho\fR packages found in \fI<dir>\fR.
.br
Scans the directory for .nho files, reads their nhoid metadata, and organizes
them into subdirectories by repository type. Generates:
.RS
.IP \(bu 4
\fIcore.packages.tar.zst\fR, \fIcore.files.tar.zst\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\fIcontent.db.zst\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\fIlastsync\fR (timestamp file)
.IP \(bu 4
\fI*.asc\fR (GPG signatures for each metadata file)
.RE
.P
Requires root privileges.

.TP
.B \-A, \-\-add-to-repo [\fB\-\-repo\-dir\fR \fI<dir>\fR] \fI<package.nho>...\fR
Incrementally add one or more \fI.nho\fR packages to an existing repository.
.br
Keeps only the latest version per package. Rebuilds affected metadata.
.br
\fB\-\-repo\-dir\fR specifies the repository root directory (required).
.P
Requires root privileges.

.TP
.B \-\-add-repo \fI<name>\fR \fI<url>\fR
Add a new repository to the nhopkg configuration. Appends the repository name
to \fBNHOPKG_ACTIVE_REPOS\fR and adds a \fBNHOPKG_REPO_<NAME>\fR variable
with the given URL.

.TP
.B \-\-remove-repo \fI<name>\fR
Remove a repository from the nhopkg configuration. Removes the name from
\fBNHOPKG_ACTIVE_REPOS\fR and comments out the corresponding
\fBNHOPKG_REPO_<NAME>\fR variable.

.TP
.B \-\-list-repos
List all currently configured repositories with their URLs.

.SS Signing & Verification
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-sign [\fB\-k\fR \fI<key>\fR] \fI<package.nho>\fR
Sign a single \fI.nho\fR package with a GPG key. If the package already has a
signature, the operation is skipped unless \fB\-\-force\fR is used (not yet
implemented). Use \fB\-k\fR to specify the signing key ID; otherwise the
default key is used.
.br
Each signing creates \fIsignature.gpg\fR inside the package. Multiple
signatures are stored as \fIsignature\-<fingerprint>.gpg\fR.

.TP
.B \-\-sign-all [\fB\-k\fR \fI<key>\fR] \fB\-\-repo\-dir\fR \fI<dir>\fR
Sign all unsigned \fI.nho\fR packages in a repository. Skips packages that
already have at least one signature. Reports counts of signed, skipped, and
failed packages.

.TP
.B \-\-verify \fI<package.nho>\fR
Verify the GPG signature(s) of a \fI.nho\fR package against the trusted
keyring. Returns success if at least one signature is valid.

.TP
.B \-\-keygen [\fB\-\-batch\fR] [\fB\-\-passphrase-file\fR \fI<file>\fR]
Generate a new GPG key for package signing. The key name is automatically
derived from the first configured repository name, or from the key id if
provided. Use \fB\-\-batch\fR and \fB\-\-passphrase-file\fR for non-interactive
(CI/CD) key generation.

.TP
.B \-\-import-key \fI<file|url>\fR
Import a public key into the trusted keyring from a local file or remote URL.
The key is added to the nhopkg signing keyring stored in
\fI/etc/nhopkg/signing\-keys/\fR.

.TP
.B \-\-export-key [\fI<id>\fR]
Export a public key from the trusted keyring to stdout. If no key ID is given,
exports the default signing key. Pipe to a file to save.

.TP
.B \-\-list-keys
List all trusted keys in the nhopkg signing keyring with their fingerprints.

.TP
.B \-\-remove-key \fI<id>\fR
Remove a key from the trusted keyring by fingerprint or key ID.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-repo\-dir \fI<dir>\fR
Repository root directory for \fB\-\-add-to-repo\fR and \fB\-\-sign-all\fR.

.TP
.B \-k, \-\-key \fI<id>\fR
Key ID or fingerprint to use for signing operations.

.TP
.B \-\-batch
Enable non-interactive (batch) mode for key generation. Suppresses GPG prompts.

.TP
.B \-\-passphrase-file \fI<file>\fR
Read the passphrase for the signing key from \fI<file>\fR. Used with
\fB\-\-batch\fR for automated signing in CI/CD environments.

.TP
.B \-\-verify-incoming
Verify GPG signatures of incoming packages during \fB\-\-add-to-repo\fR
operations. Also honored via \fBNHOPKG_VERIFY_INCOMING=yes\fR in
\fBnhopkg.conf\fR.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Create a repository from a directory of .nho files
.B nhopkg-repos \-g /path/to/packages
.TP
Add packages to an existing repository
.B nhopkg-repos \-A \-\-repo\-dir /var/www/repo *.nho
.TP
Sign a package with a specific key
.B nhopkg-repos \-s \-k 0xDEADBEEF package.nho
.TP
Sign all unsigned packages in a repository
.B nhopkg-repos \-\-sign-all \-\-repo\-dir /var/www/repo \-k 0xDEADBEEF
.TP
Verify a package signature
.B nhopkg-repos \-\-verify package.nho
.TP
Generate a key in batch mode for CI/CD
.B nhopkg-repos \-\-keygen \-\-batch \-\-passphrase-file /etc/nhopkg/passphrase
.TP
Import a key from a remote URL
.B nhopkg-repos \-\-import-key https://keyserver.example.com/pubkey.asc
.TP
List trusted keys
.B nhopkg-repos \-\-list-keys
.TP
Add and list repositories
.B nhopkg-repos \-\-add-repo myrepo https://mirror.example.com/nho && nhopkg-repos \-\-list-repos
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nhopkg (8),
.BR nhopkg.conf (5),
.BR nhopkg-src (8)
.SH AUTHOR
Jaime Gil de Sagredo Luna <jaimegildesagredo@gmail.com>
